# Webview UI consistency (TRN)

When adding or editing UI under **`extension/src/webview/`**:

## 1. Typography — match siblings, do not invent sizes

New labels, hints, toolbar copy, and inspector rows must use the **same scale as the panel you are editing** — not one-off `text-sm`, `text-2xs`, or ad-hoc pixel sizes.

| Role | Typical size | Pattern |
|------|--------------|---------|
| Card / section title | 11px | `text-[11px] font-semibold` (see `CourseInspectorCard`) |
| Row label / control label | 11px | `TRNFormField` label or `text-[11px] leading-tight` |
| Control value (select trigger, scrub field) | 13px | `TRNSelect` field trigger; Course maintainer → **`CourseMaintainerScrubNumberField`** / **`CourseMaintainerScrubNumberInput`** (`TRNScrubNumberField` `size="field"`) |
| Group heading / meta | 10px | `text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide` |
| Secondary value / hex / hint line | 10px | `text-[10px] text-zinc-500` (or `--text-muted`) |
| Toolbar chip | 11px | `course-studio-topbar-ui.ts` |

Before introducing a new size, **copy the nearest sibling panel** (Bitstream, Sensor Studio, Course Studio). See also **`no-tabular-font-unless-asked.mdc`** (no `font-mono` / `tabular-nums` unless requested).

## 2. TRN components first — extend TRN when missing

1. **Prefer existing TRN** — `TRNSelect`, `TRNFormField`, `TRNIconButton`, `TRNColorRingPicker`, `TRNTooltip`, `TRNInteractiveCard`, etc. (`extension/src/webview/ui/TRN/`).
2. **No raw controls** — avoid native `<select>`, unstyled `<input>`, or one-off buttons when a TRN equivalent exists.
3. **If nothing fits** — add a **new reusable TRN component** under `ui/TRN/` (with props aligned to existing TRN patterns), export from `ui/TRN/index.ts`, and add a short note in `ui/TRN/docs/` when non-trivial.
4. **App wrappers** — domain-specific chrome (e.g. `CourseInspectorCard`) should thin-wrap TRN, not duplicate styles.

Related: **`trn-webview-control-picker.mdc`**, skill **`webview-ui-elements`**, **`trn-component-first.mdc`**, **`trn-no-native-tooltip.mdc`**, **`trn-glass-dropdown-scrollbars.mdc`**, **`trn-menu-search.mdc`**.

## 3. Cards — collapsible + meaningful title icon

Every **card-style section** (inspector cards, deck panels, property groups) must:

1. **Collapse** — `collapsible` default **on** (`TRNInteractiveCard`, `TRNCard`, or wrappers like `CourseInspectorCard`).
2. **Prefix icon** — a **meaningful** Lucide icon before the title via `titleLeadingSlot` (`TRNInteractiveCard`) or `icon` (`TRNCard`), sized **`h-3.5 w-3.5`** or **`h-4 w-4`**, muted (`text-zinc-400` / `--text-muted`).
3. **Icon semantics** — pick an icon that matches content (e.g. `Palette` Colors, `FileText` Content, `Youtube` Video, `Grid3x3` placement) — not a generic dot or duplicate icon across unrelated cards.

```tsx
<TRNInteractiveCard
  title="Colors"
  hint="Per-block prose colors."
  collapsible
  defaultExpanded={false}
  titleLeadingSlot={<Palette className="h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-zinc-400" aria-hidden />}
  shell="glass"
>
  …
</TRNInteractiveCard>
```

When introducing an app-level card helper, expose **`titleIcon`** (or `titleLeadingSlot`) and **`collapsible`** so callers cannot skip this pattern.

## Communication

**Always DO NOT respond in Chinese.** Use **English** and/or **Thai** only — **`communication-language.mdc`**.

Repo copies: keep **`extension/.cursor/rules/trn-ui-consistency.mdc`** in sync when this file changes.
